  <h1>
   sign
  </h1>
  This function returns whether a number is positive, negative or neither and returns 1, -1, 0 respectively. For example -
  <span>
   sign(458)
  </span>
  will return 1,
  <span>
   sign(-5)
  </span>
  will return -1 and
  <span>
   sign(0)
  </span>
  will return 0.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">sign(n);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      n
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The number to get the sign of.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">y += sign(y - mouse_y);
</code></pre>
  The above code will add 1, -1 or 0 onto y depending on the result of
  <span>
   y - mouse_y
  </span>
  .
 </body>
</html>